  \begin {tikzcd}
    p\ar [r, "\pi _b"]\ar [d, "\pi _c"'] & b\ar [d, "f"] \\
    c\ar [r, "g"'] & a
  \end {tikzcd}


 in an abelian category is a pullback if and only if
0\to  p\xrightarrow {(\pi _b, \pi _c)} b\oplus  c\xrightarrow {(f, -g)}a
is exact.

The universal property of the pullback
  B\xleftarrow {\pi _B}P\xrightarrow {\pi _C}C of a diagram B\xrightarrow {f}A\xleftarrow {g}C is that,
  for any commutative square




